This will create a 3-ingredient item usually worth 80 points. Do NOT cook this 3-ingredient item further, as it will become overcooked and lose almost all its value. Submit the 3-ingredient cooked mix for 80 points. The 'water' tool can help recover some points from overcooked items, but it's best to avoid overcooking altogether.

message: Always use the 'stove' to cook raw protein (like bacon, beef, egg) and vegetable ingredients first. Combine one cooked protein with one cooked vegetable to create a valuable base. For a significant score boost, add a cooked grain (like wheat or rice) or bread as a third ingredient. Sticking to three cooked ingredients in a protein-vegetable-grain combination consistently yields high scores (e.g., 80 points). Avoid adding more than three ingredients, as this can lead to overcomplication and potentially lower scores. I did not find a use for the 'water' tool in achieving these scores.
